<p>C.W. Hooper of Keswick sent this creation to the <em>Strand</em> in <a href="https://archive.org/details/StrandVolume22/page/n235/mode/2up?view=theater">August 1901</a>: &#8220;It contains all the letters of the alphabet, twenty-six in all. They can be traced with patience. The letter N is the smallest (in the centre), and is the only indistinct one.&#8221;</p>
